<main id="content" class="content"> <header> <h1 class="title">Prayer for Ash Wednesday</h1>
 <p class="subtitle" role="doc-subtitle">Mar 01, 2017 00:00</p>
</header> <p>
Holy God,
</p>

 <p>
Shall this year be like the past, <br></br>
giving up that which brings joy, <br></br>
so that my self-imposed poverty may be <br></br>
a sign of spiritual superiority?
</p>

 <p>
Instead, Lord, <br></br>
by your grace, <br></br>
may I give up <br></br>
bitterness, arrogance, <br></br>
animosity, and the <br></br>
unwarranted certainty <br></br>
that keeps me from <br></br>
loving my neighbor.
</p>

 <p>
Cover me with your ashes, <br></br>
and raise me again <br></br>
to walk anew <br></br>
in your kingdom.
</p>

 <p>
 <i>Amen</i>
</p>


